commit.message: Upgraded from Java 11 -> Java 17 in build_apk.yml workflow

- Migrated from XML to Jetpack Compose
- Migrated `onActivityResult` to `ActivityResultsContract`
- Updated `workflows/build_apk.yml` to build and release APK
- Migrated from Groovy build scripts to KTS
- Updated `themes.xml`
- Updated `build.gradle.kts` (project-level)
- Updated package name from `com.ml.projects.age_genderdetection` to `com.ml.shubham0204.age_genderdetection`
Added workflow to build apks, on-device face detection
Added ExifInterface to handle image rotation.
Update Readme, Add Screenshots, License and PDF
Add style to buttons and background image
Add functionality to import picture from gallery
Update Readme and ipynb used for Training

Fix tests for _get_tdjson_lib_path

The previous commit 7b3423bcd2b5661515801ad1bcb8809fbd5aa3b6 broke
tests. Previously the call `find_library("libtdjson")` had always returned
*None* value. The tests were written without other values in mind. This commit
mocks the call to `find_library` to return *None* value. This way the call
to `resource_filename` can be called and checked for appropriate arguments. The `find_library` itself does not require a unit test case.

Additional changes in a file were caused by running *Black*
autoformatter as described in CONTRIBUTING.md.

Change in .gitignore was caused by running Tox testing tool as described
in CONTRIBUTING.md.

Fix find_library call

As stated in [docs.python.org](https://docs.python.org/3/library/ctypes.html#finding-shared-libraries)
... *name* is the library name without any prefix like *lib*, suffix like .so, .dylib or version number (this is the form used for the posix linker option -l)...

This way a call `find_library("libtdjson")` will never find libtdjson.so.
The correct call will be `find_library("tdjson")` so the prefix *lib*
and postfix *.so* can be added before the search.

Merge pull request #305 from weirdo-neutrino/fix_find_library

Fix tests for _get_tdjson_lib_path

The previous commit 7b3423bcd2b5661515801ad1bcb8809fbd5aa3b6 broke
tests. Previously the call `find_library("libtdjson")` had always returned
*None* value. The tests were written without other values in mind. This commit
mocks the call to `find_library` to return *None* value. This way the call
to `resource_filename` can be called and checked for appropriate arguments. The `find_library` itself does not require a unit test case.

Additional changes in a file were caused by running *Black*
autoformatter as described in CONTRIBUTING.md.

Change in .gitignore was caused by running Tox testing tool as described
in CONTRIBUTING.md.

Fix find_library call

As stated in [docs.python.org](https://docs.python.org/3/library/ctypes.html#finding-shared-libraries)
... *name* is the library name without any prefix like *lib*, suffix like .so, .dylib or version number (this is the form used for the posix linker option -l)...

This way a call `find_library("libtdjson")` will never find libtdjson.so.
The correct call will be `find_library("tdjson")` so the prefix *lib*
and postfix *.so* can be added before the search.
